 his injuries” on Thursday night, it said. [AFP] Vanguard News Nigeria By Nwafor Sunday The United States Capitol Police Chief Steven Sund, Thursday revealed that more than 50 police officers sustained injuries and are currently hospitalized following attack by some persons allegedly supporting President Donald Trump on Wednesday. Disclosing this in a statement obtained by the Journalists, the Police Chief said… January 7, 2021 In "News" A rifle-wielding opponent of President Donald Trump opened fire on US lawmakers practicing for a charity baseball game Wednesday, wounding a top Republican congressman and four others before he was fatally injured in a shootout with police. June 14, 2017 In "Crime Guard" Donald Trump said Wednesday that US police have "not been treated fairly" and appeared to defend a white officer charged with the murder of a black man. Atlanta police officer Garrett Rolfe was charged with murder Wednesday for shooting African American Rayshard Brooks in the back, and aggravated the case… June 18, 2020 In "Foreign"